Introduction to version control and git

cd desktop
mkdir (name of directory)
cd into directory
create a file =(touch file name,this is the source code)
git init
git add file =(to local repo, this is the staging area)
git commit file -m
git remote add origin (Https)
git pull = (pulls remote git to local git)
git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
git push (  git push --set-upstream origin main)




fork
git clone https address
cd into the folder
create a branch (git branch ....only creates the branch, which git checkout -b, creates the branch and switch into it)
switch to one of the branch (switch ...)
create a file: touch file (branch name)
git add
git commit -m


git branch -a =displays both local branch (main) and remote branch
git remote -v =displays (github Https)
code . =takes me vsc to writes inside the file created
git status
git add
git commit -m
git add . =adds many files at once

git log is to view commit massage
git show
(ls or ll or ls -a to display the file)
(git has both local and remote repository)
(git config user.name will display my name)
(git config user.email will display my email)I can also use the command to chnage user)

