HOW TO CREATE A PUBLIC KEYS and clone a local repo to a remote repo.
                                                                                         ON REDHAT SERVER ON TERMUIS
0. On ubuntu server terminal 
1. sudo apt update git                                                                    1. sudo yum update git
2. To clone git:ssh-keygen, enter, enter,enter to create keypair id
3. pwd
4. cd into directory of the public key
5. cd .ssh/
6. ls
7. check pwd and cd back to the right directory
7. Cat the public key id 
8. Copy the public id key
9. Go to that repo in git hub
9. Click settings, deploy keys, create new key ,title it, paste public key, tick box and save 
10. Now git clone it
11, shortcut executing a particular line :to finding the line number:first ls, then ! plus the line number eg(!14)

  
